  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "(1) Rule-based Metrics.",
    "Exact Match (EM) is a straightforward evaluation method requiring the model's output to be completely identical to the reference answer at the word level.",
    "This full character-level matching is stringent, often used in tasks requiring precise and concise answers, such as question answering systems, e.g., NQ [126], TriviaQA [115], SQuAD [232], etc.",
    "It simply calculates the ratio of perfectly matched instances to the total number of instances.For the generation of longer text sequences, BLEU [213] is a common metric initially used to evaluate the quality of machine translation.",
    "It compares the similarity between the model's output and a set of reference texts by calculating the overlap of n-grams, thereby deriving a score."
  ],
